name: RAFFLES GIRLS' SCHOOL (SECONDARY)
mrt: BRADDELL MRT, CALDECOTT MRT, MARYMOUNT MRT, BISHAN MRT

GeneralInformation.School Vision: To aspire, strive and dare to be active creators of a better age for all.
GeneralInformation.School Mission: Nurturing the high ability girl to be a leader who will realise her talents in service of nation and community.
GeneralInformation.School Philosophy, Culture and Ethos: At RGS, every student is nurtured and developed to her fullest potential. Our students journey beyond traditional boundaries in their pursuit of knowledge in a supportive environment that caters to their needs, so that they can live a fulfilling life and contribute to society.
GeneralInformation.Type of School: INDEPENDENT SCHOOL / GIRLS' SCHOOL / SINGLE SESSION

SpecialProgrammes.Special Student Development Programmes O: Providing a holistic education, our 6-year Raffles Programme (Y1-4 in RGS and Y5-6 in RI) bypasses the GCE O Level Examinations, featuring an enriched and accelerated curriculum that nurtures high-ability learners. At the end of Y6, RGS girls graduate not only with the GCE A Level Examination certificate, but also with the Raffles Diploma - designed to recognise the peaks of excellence in five domains: Cognitive, Character & Leadership, Community & Citizenship, Sports & Health, and Arts & Aesthetics.
